    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In art, refers generally to a pleasing, orderly, and consistent arrangement of the parts of a whole. The concept of aesthetic description in which architectural proportion or artistic design displays congruity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046411/Oxford Companion to Art (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese generalmente para dar a entender una disposición complacientemente ordenada y consistente de las partes de un todo. Con referencia especifícamente en arte y arquitectura, úsese para el concepto de descripción estética en que la proporción arquitectónica o diseño artístico demuestra congruencia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In het algemeen te gebruiken om een prettig georganiseerde en consequente indeling van de delen in het geheel aan te duiden. Gebruik, in het geval van kunst of architectuur, de term vooral voor het begrip van esthetische omschrijving, waarin de architectonische verhouding of het kunstzinnig ontwerp harmonie vertoont.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Na arte, refere-se geralmente a um arranjo agradável, ordenado e consistente das partes de um todo. O conceito de descrição estética em que a proporção arquitetônica ou design artístico exibe congruência. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常指部件在整體之中，呈現美好、井然有序、一致的佈局。用於指涉藝術與建築，則指建築比例或藝術設計，表現出調和一致的美感表達概念。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
